  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This UoA evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Scope: adult patients requiring cardiopulmonary bypass support, flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 1500–3500 RPM, blood viscosity per standard Newtonian approximation. Decision authority: Morrison Biomedical Simulation Group.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-cfd-hemolysis-mrl2-accepted",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-cfd-output-dataset-mrl2"
  ],
